Georgia Southern Cycling Race Weekend
description: The Georgia Southern Cycling Race Weekend will consist of registration on friday night, a criterium saturday morning, a time trial and team time trial and TTT on saturday afternoon, and a road race on sunday.
course: The courses are all relatively flat with little traffic. The criterium course has four turns in it.
registration: Please contact Tim coleman for early registration. Friday the 3 will also be early registration at the Georgia Southern recreation facility. Registration on race day will end 1 hour before race begins.
directions: From I-16 e. take exit 116 and turn left. Continue roughly 10 miles down this road (301) until you get to the 301 bypass. Turn right and make the first left at the top of the hill and you will see a sports pavillion immediately on your right.

title: University of Georgia Race Weekend
description: University of Georgia Race Weekend.  Collegiate only event.
course:
Saturday TT and RR:  24 km loop in Oglethorpe County, GA.  Race start/finish is located at the intersection of Dudley Rd and Hargrove Lake Rd.  Race will head west on Hargrove Lake Rd, taking a right onto Mitchell Farm Rd, right onto Collier Church Rd, right onto Crawford-Smithonia Rd, and a final right back onto Hargrove Lake Rd. 

Sunday Criterium: 6 turns on UGA Campus.  Sanford Drive, Green Street, DW Brooks Drive, Cedar Street.  Travelling counter clockwise.
registration: Registration is from 7:00-8:00 AM on Saturday 4/1.  First rider of TT goes at 8:30 AM.  Additional registration for crit is open from 6:30-7:00 AM on Sunday 4/2.  Men C crit starts at 7:30.
notes:
Saturday 1 April 2006:  Individual time trial begins at 8:30 AM.  Order is Men A, Men B, Women A, Men C, Women B.
Road Race begins at 1:00 AM.  Same order for TT with 5-10 minutes between groups. 

Sunday 2 April 2006:  UGA campus criterium.  Men C 7:30 AM 30 min + 3 laps, Men B 8:15 45 min + 3 laps, Women A & B 9:15 45 min + 3 laps, Men A 60 min + 3 laps.
directions:
RR and TT course:  From the Athens loop (Rt 10), take exit 8 (Lexington Rd/Oconee St).Take Lexington Rd East.  Turn left onto Winterville Rd.  Stay on Winterville Rd past the airport (~2miles).  Winterville Rd will turn into Athens Rd.  Go straight through the stoplight, crossing Cherokee Rd.  Athens Rd will turn into Smithonia Rd.  At the end of Smithonia, turn Right onto Beaverdam. At the next stop sign turn left onto Hargrove Lake Rd.  Go 2 miles to the start/finish at the top of the hill and intersection with Dudley Farm Rd.  Parking is on the left at the private residence.

Criterium course:  Directions to course: From the Athens Loop (Route 10), take the Milledge Avenue Exit and travel north (towards campus).  Turn right from Milledge Ave onto Lumpkin St.  Take Lumpkin to Cedar St and Turn right, and you will see the course in front of you.
